# Graduated Alert System Implementation

## Overview
Implement a humane, graduated alert system for cattle virtual fencing with direction detection, return path encouragement, and offline capability.

---

## Tasks

### 1. Database Schema Updates
- [ ] Add `direction` field to `LocationHistory` table
- [ ] Expand `alert_state` options in [Collars](file:///f:/Developpement/Projets/Web/Virtual-Fencing---Health-Monitoring-System/frontend/src/pages/LiveMap.js#231-239) table if needed
- [ ] Add migration/update script for existing data

### 2. Simulator (BeagleBone) Enhancements
- [ ] Add local position history tracking (SQLite)
- [ ] Implement direction detection (entering vs exiting fence)
- [ ] Implement graduated escalation logic with time delays
- [ ] Implement return path suppression (hysteresis)
- [ ] Add health monitoring integration (stress detection disables shocks)
- [ ] Add GPS accuracy buffer adjustment
- [ ] Add fence cache with offline fallback

### 3. Backend API Updates
- [ ] Modify `/api/collars/data` to store direction data
- [ ] Add direction field to latest collar endpoint
- [ ] Add endpoint for dynamic buffer adjustments (optional)

### 4. Frontend Updates
- [ ] Update [LiveMap.js](file:///f:/Developpement/Projets/Web/Virtual-Fencing---Health-Monitoring-System/frontend/src/pages/LiveMap.js) markers to show direction arrows
- [ ] Update [GeofenceAlertNotification.js](file:///f:/Developpement/Projets/Web/Virtual-Fencing---Health-Monitoring-System/frontend/src/components/GeofenceAlertNotification.js) for outside detection
- [ ] Update [Dashboard.js](file:///f:/Developpement/Projets/Web/Virtual-Fencing---Health-Monitoring-System/frontend/src/pages/Dashboard.js) activity feed for direction events
- [ ] Add visual distinction for entering vs exiting cattle

### 5. Verification
- [ ] Test graduated escalation order
- [ ] Test direction detection accuracy
- [ ] Test return path suppression
- [ ] Test offline fence caching
- [ ] Test health stress override
